NID 6 is 'TurretRoad-ExtraLight', Everything looks good.

Turret Road ExtraLight Regular (TurretRoad-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Turret Road' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight' = NID 1 'Turret Road ExtraLight'.

Pass

Turret Road Light Regular (TurretRoad-Light.ttf)

MS NID 16/17

Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Turret Road' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Turret Road Light'.

Turret Road Medium Regular (TurretRoad-Medium.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'TurretRoad-Medium', Everything looks good.

Turret Road Medium Regular (TurretRoad-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Turret Road' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Turret Road Medium'.

Turret Road Bold (TurretRoad-Bold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'TurretRoad-Bold', Everything looks good.

Pass

NID 16 'Turret Road' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Turret Road ExtraBold'.

The result of sTypoAscender – sTypoDescender (1093) match or exceed the unitsPerEm value (1000).
